While trying to refine your code I found out a few things:

1. You are a complete PHP beginner and you need a lot of practice to write standard codes. Don&#39;t worry, keep coding. It will come by time. So here goes some golden learning points for you.

2. You used while loops which was totally unnecessary here at every place. While loop is or any other loop is used only when you need to fetch all the records (or limited by coding). That&#39;s why its termed a loop. It will keep fetching the data unless it doesn&#39;t finds anymore. You should just use a simple fetch when the goal is to just use the database values individually as per the record you have selected (say record as per `where id = :id`).

3. You created unnecessary variables which was not needed. You could have directly used those values while writing queries. Parameterized queries are only needed when you are submitting data via a form as there are chances of SQL injection. For hard coding, you can enter direct values. Also, during fetch you created a variable say `$name` to store the value of `$row[&#39;names&#39;]`. Its okay but many developers do not consider it as a good practice as every variable uses a bit of memory (search google for more info). Use just `$row[&#39;names&#39;]` everywhere instead.

